That's it for the day. It was a cracking day of Test cricket, with momentum ebbing and flowing. The batsmen dominating at times, with the bowlers coming back in strongly. On occasion the spin reigned supreme, at others, express pace was more lethal. Defensive batting won the first session, while Rizwan's counter-punching and Yasir's insouciance did Pakistan much good too.

Enjoyable day to start the series, and Australia come out fresh tomorrow. I can't wait, and I look forward to joining you guys. From us for today, goodbye!
